(297, 'updated', 'model', 'updated', 'updated', 'Modules\\Contacts\\Models\\Contact', 38, 'Modules\\Users\\Models\\User', 3, 'Amit', '{\"attributes\":{\"cf_comment\":{\"label\":\"Comment\",\"value\":\"Worked as Fire Fighter and Used AFFF\\n\\nName:- Randal Paul White\\nPhone:- 8702121335\\nAddress:- 160 County Rd 778 Paragould, AR 72450\\nEmail:- fireman446346@gmail.com\\nDOB:- 01\\/22\\/1986\\n\\n\\nExposure Information\\n6. Were you exposed to AFFF (Aqueous Film Forming Foam) as a firefighter or through another occupation?\\nYes, I was exposed as a civilian firefighter support staff member.\\n\\n7. What was the name of the facility or fire department where you were exposed?\\nLafe Fire Station\\n\\n8. Please provide the physical address of the facility where you handled or were exposed to AFFF.\\n (Main St, Lafe, AR 72436) \\n\\n9. What is the contact phone number for that facility (if known)?\\n(870)\\u202f586\\u20110151\\n\\n10. When did you first begin working with or around AFFF products?\\nApril 14th 2005 (Age 19 )\\n\\n11. When did you stop using or being exposed to AFFF products?\\nDec 20th 2023  (Age 37)\\n\\n12. For how many years were you exposed to AFFF during your employment or service?\\nApproximately 18 years\\n\\nMedical History and Complications\\n13. Have you experienced any medical issues that you believe are related to AFFF exposure?\\nYes\\n\\n14. Please list all symptoms or health problems you\'ve experienced that may be connected to this exposure:\\n\\nSkin infections\\nPainful urination\\nBurning sensation during urination\\nPersistent back pain\\n\\n15. Have you undergone any medical testing or diagnostic evaluations for these symptoms?\\nYes\\n\\n16. Which of the following medical tests have you had? \\n\\u2705 Blood test\\n\\u2705 Urine test\\n\\u2705 CT scan\\n\\u2705 Biopsy\\n\\n17. What were the results of your biopsy?\\nThe biopsy confirmed the presence of Kidney Cancer \\u2013 Stage 1 \\n\\nQ. How was the biopsy test done?\\n A needle biopsy was performed on the right kidney mass under CT guidance,The tissue sample confirmed renal cell carcinoma (kidney cancer).\\n\\n18. What was your official diagnosis from your physician or oncologist?\\nKidney Cancer (Stage 1)\\n\\n19. On what date were you officially diagnosed with kidney cancer?\\nFebuary 14th 2024 (Age 38)\\n\\nTreatment and Hospitalization\\n\\n20. What is the name of the hospital where you received treatment for your condition?\\nNEA Baptist Memorial Hospital\\n\\n21. Please provide the hospital\\u2019s full address:\\n4800 East Johnson Avenue, Jonesboro, AR 72405\\n\\n22. What is the hospital\\u2019s contact phone number?\\n(870) 936-1000\\n\\n23. What is the full name of the doctor who provided your cancer treatment?\\nDr. Scott A. Dorroh ((870) 936-7000)\\n\\n24. What is your doctor\\u2019s specialty or medical field?\\nHematology & Medical Oncology\\n\\n25. Were you admitted to the hospital for treatment?\\nYes\\n\\n26. How many days were you hospitalized?\\n7 days\\n\\n27. What treatments did you receive as part of your cancer care?\\n\\n*Kidney surgery\\n\\n*Injected chemotherapy (administered in 6 cycles over 6 months) It was given in the form of IV in my left Arm \\n\\n*Prescribed antibiotics\\n\\n\\n28. What is the name of the antibiotic prescribed during treatment?\\nIntron A\\n\\n*What was done in the kidney surgery?\\n\\u27a1 A radical nephrectomy was performed on the right kidney. During surgery, the entire kidney along with surrounding fatty tissue and part of the ureter was removed to ensure all cancerous tissue was excised.\\n\\n29. When did your treatment begin?\\nFebuary 20th, 2024\\n\\nAre you cancer Free?\\nYes october 23rd 2024 I came to know that i was cancer free \\n\\nAdditional Background\\n30. Have you ever used tobacco products or had a history of smoking?\\nNo\\n\\n31. Are you currently represented by a law firm or attorney in relation to your AFFF or PFAS exposure and resulting illness?\\nNo\\n\\nHIV\\/AIDS 